<item>
            <title>[LU-13920] HSM: hsm_actions are not processed after MDS failover</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-13920</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;After each MDS failover following message could be seen:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;(mdt_coordinator.c:1116:mdt_hsm_cdt_start()) lustre-MDT0000: cannot take the layout locks needed for registered restore: -2  &lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This error means that coordinator doesn&apos;t process hsm_actions list after failover.&lt;br/&gt;
In several words the problem is caused by the race config llog processing during MDS mount. Config params that causes to start coordinator and handle hsm_actions list is processed before MDD that initializes hsm llog(mdd_prepare-&amp;gt;mdd_hsm_actions_llog_init).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Above error message could be seen after sanity-hsm_407 that does MDS failover.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
